<section class="blk blk--ink">
  <p class="eyebrow">Methodology</p>
  <h2 class="sec">How the receipts work.</h2>
  <p class="lead">Every number has a source. Every source has a date. Every model states its assumptions. Where a claim cannot be sourced, it is labeled an estimate, scenario, or hypothesis — never presented as fact.</p>
  <h3>The rules</h3>
  <ul>
    <li>Sources carry license, reuse status, and region coverage.</li>
    <li>Figures show visible &ldquo;last updated&rdquo; dates and a refresh cadence.</li>
    <li>Every correction is logged publicly.</li>
    <li>Negative results are published with the same prominence as wins.</li>
  </ul>
  <h3>Confidence labels</h3>
  <p>Confirmed · Estimate · Scenario · Needs refresh. Derived figures — calculated from two or more sources — display every contributing source, never a single badge.</p>
  <p><a href="/receipts" class="u-btn u-btn--outline-cream">The full methodology, source register, and corrections log</a></p>
</section>

